The controversial Waterkloof landing will be back in the spotlight at the state capture commission of inquiry. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Commission will on Monday hear the testimony of Former Chief of State Protocol, Ambassador Bruce Koloane. The Current Chief of state protocol, ambassador Jerry Matjila will also take the stand.
Last week, the 2013 Waterkloof Air Force Base landing for a Gupta family wedding at Sun City was on the agenda. WATCH: Focus on Guptagate at state capture inquiry Former Transport Minister Ben Martins and Chief of Air Navigation Services, Hennie Marais testified. The legal team is in the process of identifying other witnesses who will be called to appear before the Commission over the next few weeks.